Defendant Annemarie  Bottoni in court, in custody, with attorney Peter M Wolff.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant's mother and aunt address the Court.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1. 
IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT 126 DAYS IF REVOKED)
3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT; (consecutive to any other sentence);
3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Victim Impact Panel.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to Village of Hartland Police Department);

FINE:  $3039.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

TRASCRIPT FEE: $22.00 payable to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office.

DNA Fee: $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  12 MONTHS NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions.  Sentence to begin forthwith. 

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program (after serving 2 years initial confinement.)
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.(after serving 2 years initial confinement)

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

